<b>One of our staple songs - </b>5/11/01 4:59:43 PM<br>~ <b>Kaearia</b><blockquote>This song augments our role as jack-of-all-trades.  When you get this song, you can reasonably substitude for a snarer and a slower.<br><br>The slow is the same as our level 20 and 51 slows.  It starts off modestly at about 20% (attacks take 1.25x as long), but in the upper 30s jumps to about 30% (attacks take 1.43x as long).<br><br>The snare component is the best we get (51's movement slowdown is weaker, 54's equals it if you use a lute).  It too starts off fairly modest, but jumps in effectiveness somewhere in the upper 30s.  So if you're deliberately trying to slow down mobs (e.g. to ditch extra mobs while pulling outdoors), 23 is a better choice than 51.<br><br>The song now stacks correctly with the Snare and Ensnare spells, so you can keep this song on the mob to slow them even after they've been snared.<br><br>The song's duration is random.  Usually it'll last the full two ticks (about 12-18 seconds).  But sometimes it'll wear off early.  If you have a snarer in the group, you should rely on the Snare spell as your primary means of runner control and use this song only as a backup.<br><br>Another use is escaping from trains indoors, where Accelerando doesn't work.  As you run to the zone, hit esc.  That'll clear your target.  When a mob hits you, it gets automatically selected as your target.  Hit it with Chain and hit esc again.  Repeat.  As you slow the mobs to a crawl, you will outrun them and should be able to reach the zone relatively unmolested.</blockquote></td></tr><tr bgcolor="#eeeeee"><td>
